job_description:
ABOUT US

Hysata is on a mission is to accelerate the shift from fossil fuels to green hydrogen, with a disruptive approach to electrolysis.

The Hysata founding team comprises electrolyser industry veterans and the company is backed by leading cleantech investors. Our breakthrough technology has been recognised in top-tier journal Nature Communications and has created a buzz in the green hydrogen sector due to its promise to revolutionise the economics of green hydrogen production. This is possible due to Hysata’s unique combination of low capex and an ultrahigh system efficiency of 95% – a gigantic leap vs existing electrolysers which are at around 75%.

On the pathway to net-zero, green hydrogen is going to be a massive new multi-trillion-dollar global industry, of similar scale to today’s natural gas industry. With its world-beating technology and strong customer pull, Hysata is targeting becoming the leading global electrolyser player, with multi-gigawatt-scale manufacturing and putting a major dent in global emissions.

ABOUT THE POSITION

We are looking for a Data Scientist – Process Optimisation & Data Analytics to work on developing and implementing long-term interpolation, predictive maintenance, and anomaly detection models.

The Data Scientist will work within the Reliability team, primarily focusing on leveraging a variety of statistical and machine learning models to optimize process yield in our chemical production processes. The ideal candidate should have extensive experience in software development within the data science domain as well as data analysis, predictive modelling, code optimisation, unit testing and a strong interest in applying these skills to improve process efficiency and product yield.

You will thrive in the fast-paced start-up world where no two days are the same. You’ll be joining a team of smart, driven, collaborative and highly dedicated individuals who love solving engineering challenges and who are excited to be fighting the climate crisis.

POSITION RESPONSIBILITIES

 * Write high-performance, reusable, and reliable code for various data science models;
 * Optimize existing code for speed and efficiency;
 * Implement and maintain unit tests to ensure code quality and reliability;
 * Establish / improve automated data pipelines to feed ML models continually;
 * Utilize coding skills to implement models such as regression, random forest, support vector machines, XG Boost, and Neural Networks;
 * Continuously refine and adjust models based on process feedback, emphasizing code optimization and efficiency;
 * Develop code and utilise existing tools for timeseries forecasting, predictive maintenance models and anomaly detection using techniques like VAE, SVM, Isolation Forest, and/or other appropriate algorithms; and
 * Ensure that the code is scalable and can handle large datasets effectively.

ABOUT YOU

 * Degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Software Engineering, Statistics, Applied Mathematics, or a related field;
 * Strong proficiency in programming languages like Python, SQL, R, or similar, with a focus on writing clean, efficient and testable code;
 * Proven experience in software development practices, including unit testing, code reviews, and version control systems;
 * Experience with cloud infrastructure providers (e.g. AWS, Azure, Snowflake);
 * Familiarity with machine learning frameworks (e.g., AWS Sagemaker, Keras, PyTorch) and libraries (e.g., scikit-learn);
 * Good understanding of data structures, data cleaning and transformation, algorithms, data modelling, and software architecture principles;
 * Strong multitasking skills to manage multiple coding tasks and support testing simultaneously;
 * Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and debugging skills; and
 * Strong communication skills with the ability to present complex technical information to non-technical stakeholders.

WHAT'S IN IT FOR YOU?

Package: Competitive Base Salary and options

Idyllic Location

Perks Include (but are not limited to):

 * Stock options granted on successful completion of probation;
 * Salary Sacrifice into Superannuation;
 * Flexible working conditions;
 * Recognition of Service;
 * Wellness Allowance;
 * EAP – Sonder;
 * External Benefits and Perks (including Novated Leasing options) – Flare Benefits; and

Awesome work environment and a pretty cool team!

If you don’t tick every box in this ad, please don’t rule yourself out just yet. We’ve seen the research that people from underrepresented backgrounds tend to only apply when the checklist is all ticks. We take pride in inclusion and hiring incredible human beings with great potential over ticking boxes – so if this role resonates with you, apply below!

No agency contact please.
